  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research on Migration and Disability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the research study is to generate empirical findings on the nature of migration and disability in Gauteng, Limpopo and Mpumalanga provinces, South Africa. The findings will be used to support the inclusion of the needs and rights of migrants with disabilities in policies and programs. The research will be conducted in South Africa&#x2019;s economic hub, Johannesburg as well as in the border towns of Musina (Limpopo Province) and Komatipoort (Mpumalanga Province). The study will undertake a situation analysis to improve understanding of the profile of migrants with disabilities, including drivers for migration, needs, access and utilisation of key social services including health care.</narrative>
  </description>
